<Layout
  title="ByteLite Technology - We Didn't Improve Compression. We Changed the Architecture."
  description="Dictionary cascades. Szudzik pairing. Shared-model assumptions. ByteLite is engineered toward compression ratios on real-world data that would make today's best look bloated. Verification pending."
  keywords={["dictionary cascade compression", "Szudzik pairing", "shared model compression", "structured data compression", "frontier compression technology", "deterministic compression", "Hutter Prize compression"]}
  schemaType="TechArticle"
>

  <section class="technology-content">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Core Concept -->
      <div class="concept-section">
        <h2>Classical Compression Hit a Wall. We Built Around It.</h2>
        <p class="lead-text">
          Most compressors fight entropy file by file. ByteLite treats structured data as a domain:
          shared dictionaries, deterministic cascades, and a model that travels with the data.
          The result? We're chasing ratios that would rewrite the leaderboards.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Key Points -->
      <div class="key-points">
        <div class="point-card">
          <div class="point-icon">ðŸ”¬</div>
          <h3>Patent Filed</h3>
          <p>US 63/807,027 - Protecting groundbreaking compression mathematics</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="point-card">
          <div class="point-icon">ðŸ”’</div>
          <h3>Lossless Compression</h3>
          <p>Perfect data reconstruction with SHA-256 verification</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="point-card">
          <div class="point-icon">ðŸ“ˆ</div>
          <h3>Not Incremental. Architectural.</h3>
          <p>We're not chasing 10% gains. We're chasing a different order of magnitude.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Extreme Compression Section -->
      <div class="infinite-storage-section">
        <h2>What If "Compressed" Meant Something Completely Different?</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Classical compression asks: "How small can I make this file?"
          ByteLite asks: "If we share the model, how little do I actually need to send?"
          For structured data, the answer might be shockingly small.
        </p>
        
        <div class="hierarchy-demo">
          <h3>Shared-Model Compression Architecture</h3>
          <div class="compression-levels">
            <div class="level">
              <div class="level-header">The Core Insight</div>
              <div class="level-content">
                <div class="data-flow">
                  <span class="data-size">Structured data</span>
                  <span class="arrow">â†’</span>
                  <span class="compressed-size">Compact key/seed</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="level">
              <div class="level-header">How It Works</div>
              <div class="level-content">
                <p class="level-description">
                  Engine + pre-trained dictionaries = shared context<br/>
                  Only the difference needs to travel
                </p>
                <div class="data-flow">
                  <span class="data-size">Similar domain data</span>
                  <span class="arrow">â†’</span>
                  <span class="compressed-size">Dramatically smaller</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="level">
              <div class="level-header">The Target</div>
              <div class="level-content">
                <p class="level-description">
                  GB-scale corpora like enwik9<br/>
                  Represented in bytes, not megabytes
                </p>
                <div class="data-flow">
                  <span class="data-size">1GB structured corpus</span>
                  <span class="arrow">â†’</span>
                  <span class="compressed-size">Engineering goal: handful of bytes</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="level target">
              <div class="level-header">Research Phase</div>
              <div class="level-content">
                <p class="target-text">
                  1GB corpora â†’ handful of bytes. That's the engineering goal.<br/>
                  Verification will tell us how close we get.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="explanation-box">
            <h4>The Architecture</h4>
            <p>
